title: Average weekly working hours in Sweden 2019 , by type of employment
yAxis: Average number of working hours per week
summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
The Average number of working hours per week of Form of Employment Self-employed is 1.39% larger than the minimum value at Temporary employed.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
Second maximum Average number of working hours per week is found at Form of Employment Permanently employed.
The highest Form of Employment Self-employed has 9.9 more Average number of working hours per week than the lowest Form of Employment Temporary employed.

Form of Employment Self-employed is higher than any other Form of Employments with value 35.4, followed by Permanently employed, and Employed total. Down to Form of Employment Temporary employed with the lowest value 25.5.
The lowest value 25.5 at Temporary employed is almost 1.17 times smaller than the average value 30.38.
